OL,5,CNottingham react
OL,7,FWhat did the report say?
OL,9,FThe 302 report, published today,
OL,10,Fidentified a series of failings by the
OL,11,Ftrust including that the killer was
OL,12,Fnot forced to take long- lasting anti-
OL,13,Fpsychotic medication because he
OL,14,Fdisliked needles.
OL,16,FIt also found that Calocane's care
OL,17,Frisk "was not fully understood,
OL,18,Fmanaged, documented or communicated"
OL,19,Fand that there were missed
OL,20,Fopportunities to take more assertive
OL,21,Faction towards Calocane's care.
